<b>Subject:</b> Re: Kill Stealing-My take<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/quest.cgi?read=593" TARGET=_self>Kill Stealing-My take</A> (Wintermoon)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Well, I am not a warrior. I am a shaman and I hunt with 2 great

<BR>&gt; warriors every night now for a couple of months. We have
<BR>&gt; experienced the steal killing by alot of the powerful
<BR>&gt; spellcasters. Mainly in High Pass. We have come up with a couple
<BR>&gt; of ways to deal with those kill stealers. I will share our
<BR>&gt; experience with them. 1. Do not tank for them, if they attack
<BR>&gt; the same creature your engaged with, back off the creature and
<BR>&gt; let it go for the spell caster. Let all of the creatures buddies
<BR>&gt; go with him to the spell caster. (one of three things will
<BR>&gt; happen next, the caster will spend all his mana and lose a great
<BR>&gt; bit of health, the caster will run to zone or the caster will
<BR>&gt; die) the higher level casters will be around higher level
<BR>&gt; creatures. now there are some honorable casters i have come
<BR>&gt; across, although very few it seems. 2. if the caster is smart
<BR>&gt; about his kill stealing. i.e. if he casts invis on his self and
<BR>&gt; waits for you or your group to start attacking it and have it
<BR>&gt; close to half dead before he starts pounding it with spells. Try
<BR>&gt; this, have one of your party members wait for him to cast the
<BR>&gt; first spell (this will cancel his invisibility and you will be
<BR>%0
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
